The two endpoints are $(0,1)$ and $(2,2)$. This condition can be written
as:

\begin{align*}
p_1''(0) &= 0\\
p_2''(2) &=0\end{align*}

The first derivatives:

\begin{align*}
p_1'(x) &= 3a_1x^2+2b_1x+c_1 \\
p_2'(x) &= 3a_2(x-1)^2+2b_2(x-1)+c_2\end{align*}

and the second derivatives:

\begin{align*}
p_1''(x) &= 6a_1x+2b_1\Rightarrow p_1''(0)=2b_1 \\
p_2''(x) &= 6a_2(x-1)+2b_2 \Rightarrow p_2''(2)=6a_2+2b_2\end{align*}

Therefore the equations are:

\begin{align*} 2b_1 &= 0\\
6a_2+2b_2 &= 0\end{align*}
